article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 56, Morehead St. 54
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Tony Hooper scored five points in the last 54 seconds to lift Louisiana-Monroe over Morehead State 56-54 on Friday night. The Warhawks (1-0), who lost their final five games last season along with an exhibition lost to William Carey, overcame a 10-point halftime deficit. Jarvis Hill had 22 points for Louisiana-Monroe while Hooper added 14. Rudy Turner came off the bench for Louisiana-Monroe to score 10 points on 5-of-7 shooting from the field. Afam Nweke grabbed eight rebounds. Morehead State failed to score in the final 1:59 of the game. Demonte Harper missed a jumper at the buzzer that would have tied the score. Robert Murry led the Eagles (0-1) with 14 points, followed by Leon Buchanan with 13. Morehead State's Kenneth Faried had the only double-double, with 10 points and 10 rebounds before fouling out.
